ratings.question_text: What percentage of the reading and other assignments did you complete?

narratives.question_text: How well was the course organized?
comments: Paul set out the organization of the course in the opening syllabus and never deviated from the path/

narratives.question_text: How effective was the balance between instruction and discussion?
comments: Paul flows in and out of lecture and discussion flawlessly.

narratives.question_text: How well did the assigned papers, reports or other projects reflect the aims of the course?
comments: Both my project and my paper helped me to conceptualize Ibsen and Strindberg in the context of modernism.

narratives.question_text: How did the amount of assigned reading work with weekly discussion?
comments: All of our assigned readings were discussed in class.

narratives.question_text: The course filled a significant gap in your knowledge of the field.
comments: I knew very little about Ibsen and nothing about Strindberg before this semester and now I could have a well-informed conversation about either.

narratives.question_text: Regardless of whether or not the course is required, would you recommend it to other students in and outside the department?
comments: Yes, I think Paul gives a great comprehensive view of Strindberg and Ibsen and their lineage and legacy. Also a great way to read a lot of plays you should be familiar with in a condensed period.

The instructor was available for consultation, discussion and advice.
comments: Paul makes himself very available to his students for discussion and advice.

narratives.question_text: I would recommend this instructor to other students.
